249
00:26:08.360 --> 00:26:12.239
A trafficker in humans? And
you warned him about me?

250
00:26:19.538 --> 00:26:22.517
No. I told them to
leave. Not attack you.

251
00:26:22.541 --> 00:26:24.918
I would never want you
hurt. You know that.

252
00:26:25.669 --> 00:26:28.005
Where's Charlie? Is she okay?

253
00:26:33.302 --> 00:26:34.303
I don't know.

254
00:26:39.516 --> 00:26:41.536
Believe me. none of
this was my decision.

255
00:26:41.560 --> 00:26:42.644
None of what?

256
00:26:46.023 --> 00:26:47.274
Tell me.

257
00:26:48.775 --> 00:26:49.776
I can't.

258
00:26:53.488 --> 00:26:54.489
I won't.

259
00:27:03.040 --> 00:27:04.583
Stallings took Olivia.

260
00:27:05.417 --> 00:27:10.088
Not for himself or
his typical clients.

261
00:27:11.548 --> 00:27:13.359
the Davy Siegels of the world.

262
00:27:13.383 --> 00:27:17.012
No. he took her
for someone else.

263
00:27:21.058 --> 00:27:23.644
Someone I wasn't supposed to
find. Someone you're protecting.

264
00:27:28.857 --> 00:27:31.443
We're protecting.

265
00:27:35.322 --> 00:27:36.323
Ru.

266
00:27:37.241 --> 00:27:39.326
Whatever it is that's going on

267
00:27:41.411 --> 00:27:42.805
you're hurting. I can see that.

268
00:27:42.829 --> 00:27:46.041
Just help me understand.

269
00:27:53.632 --> 00:27:55.217
You have to stop
looking for her.

270
00:28:00.055 --> 00:28:01.807
I'm allowed to
tell you that much.

271
00:28:04.726 --> 00:28:05.995
Tell me.

272
00:28:06.019 --> 00:28:08.605
They need you to stop looking.

273
00:28:11.733 --> 00:28:15.696
Who's "they"? Huh? "They."

274
00:28:17.739 --> 00:28:19.259
<i>"They. Us."</i>

275
00:28:19.283 --> 00:28:20.826
And if I don't stop

276
00:28:23.161 --> 00:28:24.621
what do you think they'll do?

277
00:28:31.712 --> 00:28:32.713
I don't know.

278
00:28:44.349 --> 00:28:46.810
We have to trust that this
is for the greater good.

279
00:28:47.853 --> 00:28:51.940
All of this. everything...
Everything is for the mission.

280
00:28:56.320 --> 00:28:57.297
Sugar.

281
00:28:57.321 --> 00:28:59.948
Maybe I'll take some
of that aspirin now.

282
00:29:01.909 --> 00:29:03.535
Yeah. Yeah. of course.

283
00:29:05.329 --> 00:29:06.955
I think I have some in this...

284
00:29:13.378 --> 00:29:15.088
It's left upstairs.

285
00:29:16.423 --> 00:29:18.383
I'll be right back. okay?

286
00:29:40.781 --> 00:29:42.616
Sorry that took me
so long. I had to...

287
00:29:56.630 --> 00:29:57.631
Damn it.

288
00:29:59.424 --> 00:30:00.884
<i>Don't you love me?</i>

289
00:30:03.095 --> 00:30:07.033
That's the tough part
of it. but it'll pass.

290
00:30:07.057 --> 00:30:08.892
Most things do in time.

291
00:30:11.979 --> 00:30:12.980
<i>Oh. well.</i>

292
00:30:14.815 --> 00:30:17.025
<i>Not the first time my
heart's been broken.</i>

293
00:30:18.944 --> 00:30:22.573
<i>I should have known. I
should have seen the signs.</i>

294
00:30:24.616 --> 00:30:26.761
You're in a bad way. my boy.
Let me get you something.

295
00:30:26.785 --> 00:30:28.370
No. Thanks. anyway.

296
00:30:29.246 --> 00:30:34.168
<i>But this case. I got too close.
Just like they said I would.</i>

297
00:30:39.256 --> 00:30:41.884
<i>Too late now. I'm in.</i>

298
00:30:44.928 --> 00:30:46.346
<i>Let them come after me.</i>

299
00:30:48.599 --> 00:30:49.933
<i>I'm not stopping.</i>

300
00:30:54.354 --> 00:30:59.276
<i>Maybe tonight... Maybe it's
okay to take a little break.</i>

301
00:31:04.448 --> 00:31:06.909
<i>Just a tiny little break.</i>

302
00:31:09.244 --> 00:31:10.454
<i>Just for tonight.</i>

303
00:31:11.997 --> 00:31:13.081
<i>go home.</i>

304
00:31:16.627 --> 00:31:17.836
<i>Go home.</i>

305
00:31:18.305 --> 00:32:18.822
